      <hedline>
        <hl1>Climate Policy: Heat and Sparks</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Kinnan O'Connell letter says that if people lead effort to forestall global warming, leaders will have no choice but to follow (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Bob Herbert's June 6 column, ''Ignoring a Growing Peril,'' makes clear that the people will have to lead the effort to forestall global warming. This means using less energy, driving smaller cars, keeping the house warmer in summer and cooler in winter and so on.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Bob Herbert's June 6 column, ''Ignoring a Growing Peril,'' makes clear that the people will have to lead the effort to forestall global warming. This means using less energy, driving smaller cars, keeping the house warmer in summer and cooler in winter and so on.</p>
        <p>As in the past, if the people lead, the leaders will have no choice but to follow.</p>
        <p>KINNAN O'CONNELL  Larchmont, N.Y., June 6, 2002</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
